Optimize the application bundle by introducing structured code-splitting and dynamic imports.

==================================================
PRIMARY OBJECTIVE
==================================================

Reduce the initial bundle size and improve first-load performance without changing the current UI or workflow behavior.

A build warning shows that the main bundle is too large.
We want a targeted optimization pass using dynamic import().

==================================================
PHASE 1 — SPLIT BY WORKFLOW STEP
==================================================

Refactor the main protocol workflow so each major step loads as its own chunk.

Create separate lazy-loaded modules for:

- Patient Definition
- Protocol Selection
- Safety Validation
- Treatment Timeline
- Final Review
- Export
- Protocol Dashboard
- Admin Tools

Use lazy loading / dynamic import for these screens.

==================================================
PHASE 2 — SPLIT HEAVY CLINICAL MODULES
==================================================

Identify heavy business logic modules and load them only when needed.

Candidates include:

- timeline generation engine
- safety rules engine
- protocol comparison logic
- confidence scoring engine
- PDF export generator
- ICS export generator
- JSON export formatter

These should not be bundled into the initial app load.

==================================================
PHASE 3 — REMOVE STATIC DATA FROM MAIN BUNDLE
==================================================

Audit whether protocol definitions, FAQs, products, or clinical templates are embedded in frontend JavaScript.

If so:

- move them to Firebase / backend source
- fetch them on demand
- cache after load

Do not keep large protocol/template datasets in the main UI bundle.

==================================================
PHASE 4 — PREFETCH NEXT STEP
==================================================

After code-splitting, add smart prefetching for the next likely workflow step.

Examples:

- Step 1 completed → preload Step 2
- Protocol selected → preload Safety step
- Timeline entered → preload Review step

This should improve navigation speed without increasing first-load cost.

==================================================
PHASE 5 — KEEP USER EXPERIENCE STABLE
==================================================

Do not change:

- current workflow behavior
- current layout
- current visual design

Add appropriate loading fallbacks for lazy-loaded screens.

Use lightweight loading states.

==================================================
PHASE 6 — DELIVER PERFORMANCE REPORT
==================================================

After implementation, provide a short summary of:

- what was split
- what remains in the main bundle
- expected bundle size reduction
- recommended next optimization targets

==================================================
FINAL OBJECTIVE
==================================================

Create a smaller initial bundle and a faster-loading application by splitting workflow screens, heavy clinical engines, and export modules into on-demand chunks.